PARLIAMENT IS suspended for weeks. The Conservative party has been hollowed out. The prime minister’s hopes for an election have been dashed, twice. What does all this portend for the Tory party? And a special election in a solidly Republican district in North Carolina may shed light on President Donald Trump’s re-election chances. Also, a look at the unsung human superpower of language. Runtime: 20 min    Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn